
[1]palliation

   PALLIA'TION, n. The act of palliating; concealment of the most flagrant
   circumstances of an offense; extenuation by favorable representation;
   as the palliation of faults, offenses, vices or crimes.

   1. Mitigation; alleviation; abatement; as of a disease.
